  "prompt": "Did islam exist before prophet mohmmad?",
  "response": "Islam, as it is known today, originated with the Prophet Muhammad in the 7th century CE in the Arabian Peninsula. However, Muslims believe that the core message of Islam\u2014submission to the will of Allah (God)\u2014has existed since the beginning of humanity. According to Islamic belief, previous prophets, such as Adam, Noah, Abraham, Moses, and Jesus, all preached the same fundamental message of monotheism and submission to God, which is seen as the essence of Islam.\n\nThe term \"Islam\" was not used to describe a formalized religion in the way it is today until the revelation received by Prophet Muhammad, which was recorded in the Quran. However, the followers believe that the principles of Islam have been present throughout history and that the revelations to Muhammad were the final and complete form of this guidance.",
